<item>
            <title>[SPR-2767] Circular reference of request scoped beans throws OutOfMemoryError or infinite loop.</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2767</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If I have two request scoped beans who reference each other when I attempt to load one of those beans I get an OutOfMemoryException because of an infinite loop.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;bean name=&quot;someBean&quot; scope=&quot;request&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;property name=&quot;someOtherBean&quot; ref=&quot;someOtherBean&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/bean&amp;gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;bean name=&quot;someOtherBean&quot; scope=&quot;request&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;property name=&quot;someBean&quot; ref=&quot;someBean&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/bean&amp;gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Even if circular references of non singleton scoped beans is not supported we should probably not have an infinite loop if it&apos;s possible to avoid.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mike&lt;/p&gt;</description>
